African National Congress (ANC) presidential hopeful Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma's campaign in the North West Province was brought to an abrupt halt after she was chased away from the site of the Marikana massacre by Association of Mineworkers and Construction Union (AMCU) members.Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma and hundreds of ANCWL members have now left Marikana after AMCU members chased them off. @HuffPostSA.BREAKING: AMCU members have chased off Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma and the ANCWL from Marikana. @HuffPostSABREAKING: Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma did not even exit her car when her entourage was turned away by AMCU members at Marikana. @HuffPostSAAMCU members say they will not allow Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma to use the Marikana massacre to her political advantage. @HuffPostSAThe situation was tense at Marikana. ANCWL leaders told their supporters to disperse to avoid conflict. @HuffPostSA NDZ left in a hurry.